 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Director/Senior Director, Discovery Chemistry (f/m/d) atai New York State Remote Full-time Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Director/Senior Director, Discovery Chemistry 
 
Location:  NYC Hub; London; Berlin (remote hybrid/travel) 
 
Position:  Full-time 
 
atai Life Sciences is a biopharmaceutical company focused on developing innovative treatments and processes to treat mental health disorders for everyone, everywhere. We operate a decentralized model whereby atai incubates, acquires, and supports individual platform companies by providing them strategic and operational functions centrally, allowing our platform companies to stay lean and agile in their clinical pursuits, whilst also being able to leverage the expertise of a multibillion-dollar global biotechnology company. Atai is pursuing a world-first strategy to deploy our clinical compounds alongside a clinically validated digital ecosystem which aims utilizes cutting edge technology, clinical protocol, human-interaction psychology, and data science to enhance the clinical efficacy and engagement of our compounds. 
 
Who you are: 
 
 You have a demonstrated ability to attend to multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment without losing focus of the larger goal. 
 You thrive in a global, dynamic, highly complex environment. You are comfortable working with a global team across time zones, different cultures, and various local rules and regulations. 
 You have strong analytical and organizational skills to set strategy and translate strategy into tactics. 
 You overcome obstacles collaboratively while respecting others' points of view, and you empower your team to be creative and resourceful. 
 You are always learning and are always well informed on the state-of-the-art in your discipline. 
 You are internally motivated to implement best practices in a continuous cycle of improvement. 
 You can inspire, coach and lead project teams to meet project deadlines. 
 
 Opportunity: 
 
 
 Work in a fast-paced, matrix organizational environment where you'll work on a wide range of topics and cross-collaborate across teams 
 Work with world-class scientists and clinicians in the development of psychedelics and other innovative experimental drugs in several psychiatric and CNS indications 
 Lead the company's Discovery efforts, identifying novel chemical matter, contributing to the company's intellectual property position and acting as atai's resident medicinal chemistry expert. 
 Report to the VP of Early Development and be an integral part of a growing CNS-focused early development team 
 Work out of multiple hub locations with great office space (Berlin, London, NYC, San Diego), providing the ability to work from where you want with the device and equipment you choose 
 Participate in company retreats in Europe and USAwith a global team and supportive culture 
 Competitive stock option plan, employee benefits and health/wellness programs 
 
 Responsibilities: 
 
 Discover and advance novel small molecule drugs into clinical development 
 Strategically plan, manage, oversee and/or execute discovery activities including AI molecular design efforts, in silico and receptor-based screening and novel discovery paradigms based on new target-centric insights 
 Provide strategic, scientific, and managerial leadership for atai's medicinal chemistry programs 
 Define, implement, and execute on medicinal chemistry strategies to urgently advance hit-to-lead optimization efforts and prioritize candidate compounds for clinical developments 
 Serve as internal chemistry expert for discovery, medicinal chemistry and early CMC activities as required 
 Oversee discovery and chemistry CROs and other external resources, and ensure quality results are delivered on time and within budget. This includes active vendor management of discovery and medicinal chemistry vendors, compound management, compound profiling, data analysis, interpretation and presentation 
 Participate in a highly collaborative environment working closely with pharmacology stakeholders and atai's development team to rapidly identify and prioritize hits for follow-up 
 Work with IP team to create and execute strategy to establish, protect and expand intellectual property. 
 Communicate, collaborate, and coordinate effectively with cross-functional teams 
 Prepare, review and deliver high quality scientific presentations for internal/external use 
 Lead multidisciplinary drug discovery project teams in a fast-paced, results-driven biotech environment 
 
 Qualifications: 
 
 Ph.D. in Organic Chemistry or Medicinal Chemistry with 10+ years of drug discovery experience in the biotech/pharmaceutical industry 
 A strong track record of medicinal chemistry successes in hit-to-lead optimization and delivery of clinical candidates 
 Broad background in all aspects of drug discovery, with working knowledge of structural biology, computational screening approaches, screening cascades, ADME/PK, in vitro assays, and in vivo pharmacology 
 Experience in managing chemistry CRO activities and academic collaborators; demonstrated ability to negotiate contracts, develop study protocols and on-time delivery of study reports supporting development candidate nomination and regulatory submissions 
 Strong organizational, interpersonal, communication, and managerial skills that motivate and inspire others to achieve corporate scientific objectives 
